0 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Italy thinks I want to join him in taking you out, so hopefully I can get some inside info from Italy to help us out this season. Are you leaning one way or another right now or do you want to wait to hear what Italy says? Italy may know I'm with you, so not sure how much we can trust anything Italy says, but I will pass on what I hear.
1 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: I am leaning to Austria (and hoping he tells Italy) that I am really pissed with you and will make my best to not let you take my centers. I didn&t try to do this directly with Italy because we haven&t talked much lately and it will be really suspect.
Will wait on you to set the moves, but maybe Pic to Bel with NS and Bur support and Gas and MAO support Spa while Brest move to EC could be a good option.
2 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: I tried to get info from Italy by suggesting Brest hit Gas while West Med support MAO to Spain, but Italy wants me to support him to Spain and use Brest to hit Gas, so my response was that I need a build this year and if he'd help me with that. If I were against you, I think that's a reasonable conversation, so I'm trying to make it look as real as possible! ;)

Good work with Austria, I'm sure that will be passed on to Italy!

I like the idea of North Sea and Bur supporting Pic to Bel as well as your other ideas, though I'll have to try and balance North Sea with Russian efforts. Russia REALLY wants us to insure you do not lose Bur this spring, though if Germany gets into Bur he starts to get overextended a bit for defending his north and from Russia possibly attacking Silesia this spring.

We really do need these 48 hour phases, gives us plenty of time to get on track. I'll be in touch.
3 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Well, the main problem with Germany taking Bur is that I cannot hold Spa on this situation as he can cut Gas support. So maybe it&s better Pic support hold Bur while Brest move to EC and we have a decent chance to put you into Bel on the Fall without risking to lose nothing.
4 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: I agree, Pic will support hold at Bur. MAO will support hold at Spain and Gas should also support hold at Spain since Italy tells me Westmed and Lyo will support Mar to Spain. I will send Italy a message to encourage him to do that so that our defenses hold. I am pretending with Italy I am on his side to increase the odds of our success this season, I hope it works since if it does we will be in great shape for fall! :)
5 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: I suppose another option is for Spain to support Bur to Mar, since MAO and Gas will support hold at Spain and Italy tells me West Med and Lyo are supporting Mar to Spain, this would kill that army since Ven is attacking Pie. The main problem being that Germany will likely support an attack on Bur. Pic is still updated to support hold at Bur, but if you want to give taking Bur to Mar a shot, then let me know and I'll have Pic attack Bel in case Italy changes things up and you don't get Mar, to counter Bel supporting Mun to Bur, which is likely what Germany will order along with Hol supporting hold at Bel.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Here's what I propose: Let me move Ven back to Pie. You support yourself to Ven. I have a unit to spare, so that won't hurt me. Hold off on taking London for this turn, and take it next year. In the meantime, I can work my army back to Paris, as per our exchange, and then England will be dead so I can move my fleets south while you take those centers.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: ?This makes no sense?

Ok, I guess the others talked a lot. But let's go through this one by one:
1. Why move back to PIE? You will place in MAR anyway next turn and can then go back to take PAR and BRE? This is a full retreat and you're giving them a center. I cannot support myself to VEN alone - it's 2 vs. 3 if TRI helps.

2. You don't want me to take LON, but are ok to lose another center? Come on, you can't expect me to be ok with this in any way. What is the point? I don't want to lie to you, I'm moving as I told you - GAS-BUR, BUR-MUN, NS-LON, HOL-NS with support from NOR. I am in a position where I really think I don't need to lie to you.

3. Look, my main objective for this game was to make up for missing game 1. I can achieve this with a 3-way or 2-way draw also. I know that getting a solo will have implications, it always does...

Anyway, my point is simple - I have a stalemate line against the East. They can't do anything to me, nor can they help you in any way. I don't want to fight you, as this will only lead me to a draw. However, we need to keep pushing east.

For all practical purposes if you control the Mediterranean you can always stalemate me there, so you will hold me hostage if I decide to attack you in full.

It is in your interest to take Italy, I am not joking about this. Look at the map and you will see that this will give you value and power that you do not have currently against me. If we fight now you'll die, and I have a good shot at finding other allies on similar terms, a lot of people are desperate in this situation.

I am really not ok with retreating from Italy. This will be a huge mistake and you're not doing yourself a favor. TUN and VEN are exactly the reason I am interested in working with you, otherwise I would have accepted AUS/It's offer of a 3-way draw a long time ago.

I'd strongly suggest that you stick with me on this one. Unless I'm missing something it will be plain wrong to go against me at this point. I have no problem with you planning for your 'independence', it's only normal, but let's be smart and not lose the game over it.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I'm not losing the game over it. The retreat from Ven was not a proposition to go against you. You have a glut of armies, and if you are indeed moving out, you will have enough to take Italy. I was not thinking about a build...poor calculations on my part. Like I said before, I look at this map for about 5 minutes a day. I'm far from in form here.

Obviously I lose if I fight you. I'm not thick. But you are nearly accusing me of turning against you, when all actions I have done have been in support of you. You moved into my homeland, and I supported you. You then took my home centers against my wishes, and I supported you. You then moved south which serves no purpose but to launch at attack on Spain and Mar, and now I am the one who is being called into question for raising some minor concerns about my remaining centers? At what point did that sound like me attacking you?

I have fleets all over the Med that over power all others. I have no means of opposing you on land. Please stop threatening me with ultimatums. You don't want me to move to Pie? Fine. I will take your support to Rome. You take London, I take Edi, I build in Mar, I take back my centers.

Watch. This is me trusting you again. Again. And again. If I were judging by past moves, one would assume that Mar will be gone next turn. But this is my attempt again to prove myself wrong. Let's see what happens.
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Sorry if I was too harsh. I have no issue with anything you've done so far and know you've done nothing against me the whole game. I just reacted like this because what you suggested was not optimal and it sounded like an ultimatum itself - I couldn't just agree to it.

As for you trusting me - I know I cannot expect this from you - so I'm asking you to trust me, I am trying to explain how I see things, so that we can reach a logical conclusion and move in a way that is constructive for both. Forget the trust, let's approach this more pragmatically.

I have pushed the others into the corner without any ability to react, you can go all the way to TUR and we can eliminate everyone else if they don't get organized soon. They way things are going this may very well end up as a 2-way draw.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: So, do you think Ank will support Con to Smy, or that Ank and Black Sea will support hold at Con? If Ank supports Con to Smy, Aeg should support hold at Smy while Smy supports Bul to Con and Greece supports Serb to Bul, that will get you Con. I'm sure Arm will support hold at Sev, so if Black Sea and Ank support hold at Con, we likely won't get Con regardless, so I'll input those orders unless you suggest otherwise.
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: First of all, sorry for not getting back to you sooner. Life has been hectic as usual and I've been seriously neglecting the game.

That is an interesting set of messages. It's not too surprising to hear that from Germany, as he is a crafty player and would do what he can diplomatically to improve his chance of potential solo, or at least strengthen his position to insure his share of the draw. However, England also echoing that concern and specifically predicting that Germany would be sending that message is an interesting play. England is quite a skilled and intelligent player as well. His ability to diplomatically deflect the 3v1 situation that he was facing is quite a testament to that, and I certainly think he is aware that a strong CPA has formed. With a strong CPA, he knows he can't make it to the draw, but at the same time, he can't just come out and attack Germany and risk further galvanizing our alliance. His best play would be to create internal tension within our alliance to try to rip us apart, while working with Germany for the time being to possibly strengthen his position to be included in the draw.

I have no grand delusions of a solo in this game. It's quite clear that you, Germany, and England are far too experienced let something like that happen. I believe the best play for me and for our CPA is to work toward the 3-way draw. Getting England out of the picture may be tricky, but I think we will be able to accomplish that. I concur with your observation that we have the failsafe of establishing the corner stalemate position (provided that we eventually clean Turkey and Russia out of that area) in order to prevent any possible ambitions of an EG alliance. However, I think that Germany is also aware that any long-term partnership with England is not in his best interests, as none of us want to see our 3-way draw turn into a 4-way draw, and hopefully he doesn't have any ambitions to leverage a partnership with England to set up for a solo attempt, which I think would only make a great mess of things.

By the way, England and Germany did not mention anything to me about watching out for an Italian solo. Actually, England has been trying to pit me against Germany, telling me that he thinks that Germany may try to solo and that we need to unite to squash that threat. I imagine that England is also talking to Germany trying to pit him against you, in order to negotiate his way into the draw possibly with you cut out of the picture. England needs to expand into France to strengthen his position and working with Germany is the only way to accomplish that.

Ok, that's enough paranoia and speculation for now. I think the less paranoid interpretation of the situation strongly reinforces the notion that Germany is committed to the CPA. Before the spring moves, he was facing potential hostility from E, F and R, but he was able to diplomatically influence England into making moves that went quite well for Germany. He moved into Sweden and can take Norway this fall as well. If he follows through with that, it'll be devastating blow on England and remove any worries about England and Germany.
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Ok, as for moves: Yes, I agree that your suggestion would probably be best. It's a safe set of orders that guarantees Smy and a Turkish disband and makes a safe play on Con if Turkey does something stupid. However, it's probably most likely that Turkey will just hold Con with support from Bla and Ank.
Just to reiterate:
Gre S Ser -> Bul
Smy S Bul -> Con
Aeg S Smy

By the way, I offered Turkey support into Sev last turn and I actually issued that order. I'll offer the same thing to him again (but I won't actually give the order this time). It would be ideal for us if used Ank to cut Arm and attacked Sev with Bla, but I know it's quite a long shot.
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: All sounds perfect, great analysiss, I'm excited we are so in tune to each other's way of thinking. I too pefer to see this CPA to the end, so will try to check my paranoia. I've got along well with Germany, and even though England is trying to pull me on his side, I will just play nice long enough to get Germany and me into position to take him down. All's looking good and I've submitted those orders we discussed. Good luck with Russia and the north!
4 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Germany is saying that the other powers are telling him that you and I have been trying to undermine him diplomatically. He seems quite annoyed, but it seems that he'll may likely give us the benefit of the doubt. I'm trying to reassure him.
5 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: He sent me a major paranoid message too. My bet is England is making some guesses and pushing his buttons. I sent Germany a long message telling him I'm 100% behind the CPA, which I am, I'm just 200% behind our alliance, so if he freaks out and does something crazy then we have the option to pull in someone else, I just hope he can keep it together.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: Thank you for your detailed response, I will try to be as detailed in mine.

Indeed, you have a difficult posture due to my position in the North - but this also assures me that I have the upper hand for now and can handle a two front war with RF if need be. I appreciate that you are willing to set aside your unease and work in concert. I will not let you down so easily.

on burgundy - part of it was to assure you of my intent and motivation. part of it was to counter a potential French stab that I was concerned with. regarding russia - you can lay your heart at east on that front as well. I have a some tricks up my sleeve that you will be happy with, but just like the burgundy situation, i'd rather not divulge them as it does not benefit either of us.

however, I do have some 'marching orders' for you to consider... I want you to move Sweden to Norway. this will be KEY in making sure we get what we want and will likely produce a build for you this year. so please trust me. I am sorry I can not divulge ALL my moves to you nor tell you what Russia's moves are for fear that you will change your moves. if we continue down this path of trust and I do not see you turning on me with French (or Russian) help, then in a short season as you see my moves and I see your further commitment, then I can tell you the why and how of the moves as well. I know this is a big request, but as you said yourself, if I was going to stab you for a measly gain in edi and to be stuck between russia and france, I could do that anyways right? so please trust me.

in the south, York to Lvp is critical and I expect it to get in.

I think either wal or lon to ech can work fine. but I personally think Lon to Ech is much more important right now. yes, you want to get north and I will readily cede it to you but first and foremost, I hope you take Irish. the main reason I say not to move wal is that there is a scenario under which wal may be needed to cover liverpool in the fall and if you don't have the unit in wal, it could throw my ability to help you take norway difficult.

in the end, i wont be prickly on this particular point, for now I will put in North support London to Ech, but after you have considered things further, if you still feel you MUST move wal, then I will change my support. but Swe to Nwy and York to Lvp are key.

as for my own moves in the south, suffice to say that I do not want to give you my moves for the same reasons you outlined yourself. no gain for you and if france blocks me then it would make me doubt you right? so best not to worry about it.

like I said, I have reason to believe that russia will not have the free hand in the south that he hopes to have. let me leave it at that.

I'm committed to us... in great part because I can write you a long message like this and I know you'll respond in kind - with detail and expertise. I like that and find that games with partners such as you are far more fun and enjoyable than games with partners who write a few lines and can't think in abstract terms about the 'bigger picture' or about strategy. so thanks for your diplomatic style. ;)
1 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: Thanks for the message. I'm sadly not able to reply now and likely won't be in a position to do so until tomorrow. You will hear from me as soon as I can sit down at the cpu and think things through for a minute.
2 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: no problem. we have 28 hrs
3 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: Yeah... Sorry I can't get to this now... My mental space is full of ... real life issues. I hope those will clear sufficiently enough by tomorrow morning.
4 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: So I've read your message again with a clearer mind and here's what I have to say.

You're asking an awful lot out of me! You're more or less asking me to walk blinded through a tight and twisting corridor with only sparse words coming from you to aid my progress... I'm not comfortable with this and it's not something I'll keep doing for much longer, as I'm sure you'll understand (and your message seems to indicate that you're aware of that, so I'm not too worried).

Swe will go to Nor, Yor to Liv, Lon to Channel and Wales to Irish. The last move will either bounce and cover both the Irish and Wales, or set me up to take MAO in a year or two. The first alternative is more likely...

Russia trusts you a lot, but is nonetheless plotting your demise. I'm not saying that so to gain your trust as there's really not much for me to do on that front: either you're in fact allied with me or you're not, but it's not a question of trust that will decide that for you at this point. No, it's more simply that I'm trying to help the person I consider my ally be aware of possible dangers. Russia has explicitly talked about how we share an interest in controlling your growth. He would have me move in such a way as to force you into a tough spot in the fall, more or less forced to support him into Sweden (which he is convinced you will do).

France is not trustworthy and I'm not hearing much about him from other powers. As far as I know from what he told me, his plan is still to set himself up against you and vacate my seas. Like I said, I put very little faith in his words, but I did see them as an opportunity to throw the WT out there once more. I told him that we had not yet suffered too greatly at the hands of one another and that our positions are still quite solid if we were to decide for that kind of strategy. His reply was that we needed, among other things, to break AR and see to it that Italy doesn't have much to hope from A or T.

A WT could still be tempting to me, of course, but for now I'm only committed to this. I suggest we see how the next phase turn out where France is concerned and sell the WT if it seems likely that he'll play for it. Once the WT is on track, if that should happen, you and I would need to work right away on how we would take France out of the mix...

I take great comfort in your words and find many reasons in your messages to believe that you are indeed as dedicated to EG as I am. I'd like to offer more input, but since you seem to have the situation quite under control and do not feel ready to share intel with me, there's not much I can say that wouldn't ring like futile assumptions.
5 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: Thank u for ur trust. U will not be dissapointed. I can promise that.

After this turn, france will no longer trust me and u will be in ech for sure. Russia will still think I'm with him and will get a rude surprise in the fall.

Thanks again for ur trust

I'm trying to use the situation to our advantage in the southwest, trying to get a little room to operate for France and myself, so we'll see if Italy goes for it.

Please make no mistake, I am 100% a part of the Four Corner Alliance and view A/I to be just as culpable for the German's actions as the German himself, since Germany needed A/I to be his allies in order to stab me.
1 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: Again, I'm all for you having Den, all I care about is taking down Germany and his A/I/G. 3 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Thanks!
4 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: No problem, THANK YOU for helping me attack Germany, the German's loss is the Fca's gain!

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: What do you want to do this fall? I could try supporting your fleet into Con. Could you support hold Bul with Gre?
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: By the way, Germany really wants me to do my best to convince you to support him into Mar. I'm sure he's already made his case to you, so I'm not really sure what I can add. Do whatever you feel is best.

He's certainly been playing a very strong game. He has France asking for permission before responding to press and even Russia (and now me, ha) relaying messages for him.
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Sorry, been entertaining the in-laws...

Greece will absolutely support hold at Bul, of course, that unit will do whatever you request since you gave that to me! I like the idea of Aeg tapping Con and Bul supporting that, even if it is doomed to failure, gives our units something useful to do, so yeah, let's do that.

The German is a bit overstretched, it appears he has taken on both England and France, so I think it's likely best for me to help him into Mar, especially since he will be in position to help you with Russia sooner that way, then we just have to make sure we can stalemate him before he goes for a solo.

Let me know if you have any other thoughts, I will check in about an hour before the phase goes through. Thanks again for your patience with my limite time of late, it will get better, but the in-laws aren't leaving until Friday now.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Excellent, glad to hear that. I'll put in the orders as discussed.

intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Hey, thanks for keeping your word. I know you didn't have to, and you had promised Turkey to help him. To be honest, I didn't expect you to, but I'm glad you did. You were really my only hope in this game, and I'm glad to see I still have that. :-)
1 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: You can certainly help by assisting in the removal of the French and we can call it an end game. To be honest, I don't fully trust that Turkey and Italy are going to 3-way. Italy's probably telling me the truth, but I can't say that Turkey is up for it completely.
2 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: I'd like to see you, me, and Italy in the three-way at this point. But getting there is going to require my working with Italy. Which is going to be somewhat difficult.
3 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Are you moving to Boh by the way? Because we still need another army over there for the stalemate.

I'd recommend a self bounce in Boh, but it's entirely your call.
4 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: I don't see that happening. I think Turkey is pretty well dug into his position. You can certainly try and I'll secure the north with your fleet if you do. You can also use my army in Silesia as well.
5 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Well if he moves to Boh and Rum to Gal, he can force Ukr, and then Warsaw.

PIE hold
VEN support PIE

UKR to WAR
ION to TYR
AEG to ION
NAP sup.m to TYR f ION

I'd assume you'll get a full build this turn if he does go for the North again, with Holland, London, and Liverpool. That will be a huge swing.

0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I think you're gonna want A Vie.
I'll support Alb into Greece, but remember at some point I'd like to scoop that SC up. Army Syria is moving to Smyrna. I'd appreciate either a support or an attack on Con.
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: I don't have a build! Yeah, you can get Greece eventually, but for now we both need to grow and shouldn't be too focused on you taking Greece, we need to just kill off Turkey and get ready for Russia and make sure France doesn't turn on you.

Aeg is attacking Con, that way I don't need to know which unit you are supporting into Smy, and you can change it up if you want at any time without coordinating with me.
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Are you trying to talk Russia into working with us? I hope so, I think the F/G will be heading our way soon and our only chance is an eastern triple. England is all but dead and if we don't kill Turkey quickly and get on the southeast stalemate line quickly we'll both join the Turk shortly thereafter. I'm making any argument I can think of to the Russian, including throwing out ideas that you and I don't fully trust each other, so the Russian doesn't think we'll just quickly turn on him once Turkey is dead... which we will do, of course, if we can, but I'm thinking the F/G will require us to work with the Russian... Thoughts?
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: It all makes sense. If possible, get the Russian to contact the English. He looks cd, but maybe he'd start fighting again if he knew he had an ally. If England fought, especially helped by Russia, it would slow F/G down.
I can pin the German down. I thought maybe we could get him in on an Anti-russian attack, but it's tough to trust him. He spent the past couple turns encouraging me to attack France and then helping France, which means... what? He's either trying to get intel off me to help his friend or he's trying to get me to hobble his rival. If it's the second option, we may still have a shot at turning him.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I'll talk to Russia and see what I can see.
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: All sounds great, thanks for the effort, we're going to have to give this game all we got if we want to survive!

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> TURKEY: So I see you've been persuaded by Austria to join him. I don't blame you; you were trapped in that corner with nowhere to go, however I wonder where he could be offering you Scs in return for your help. He is so much larger he could basically take what he wants from me.

In addition, he's stabbed you before, and is highly likely to do so again. Be under no illusion that if and when my threat is neutralised he will turn right around and gobble you up. In your position as you were last turn you were basically secure; he couldn't defeat you without another fleet bordering Smyr, which I would have easily stopped. Now you're much more vulnerable.

I'd love it if you could reconsider your decision and join our side. England, France and I are already working together as I'm sure you've deduced, and we're set to win the fight quite easily at the moment. Our alliance was formed to stop the Austria-germany alliance, and as such our current agreement is a three way draw. We would be very willing to open that to a four way on the same understanding. As for your possible SC gains, Bulgaria, Greece, Rumania and Sevastopol would be obvious locations for Turkish occupation. Let me know your thoughts.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: I was hoping to speak to you actually. Austria has betrayed me twice, and now it is my turn to betray them. I have given the illusion that we are in am alliance, but I only said that so.he would free up units from around me. Now I am much more set up to attack him if I so wish.

Make no mistake, I am fully against him. Tell me what you need me to do and I would love to end in a draw with the three of you.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: Excellent. Well obviously at the moment I need you to prove your intentions so I'll leave that to you, but might I suggest slipping Aeg into Bul and Eastern to Aeg? It guarantees you a build and will split Austria's attention nicely.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: That was my original plan.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: the baltic sea ?

care to explain what business you would have in the baltic sea ?

don#t tell me you have fallen for englands desperate pleads. look at the map. france is my ally. like that, england will be completely annihilated within the next 2 years. meanwhile turkey seems to making a more concentrated effort on defeating you.

once england is dead, I have to chose between france, austria or you.

I would ask you to reconsider what you are doing there, or I might chose you.

there is no reason for us to fight, and just because england is getting desperate does not mean you have to jump to his aid "because that fleet has nothing better to do"

even if you get berlin, how long do you think you will be able to keep it ? with warsaw and moscow locked down by turkey, you should not start war on a second front. it's self-distructive

I would advice talking to austria instead

he is visibly nervous. turkey is getting units into position, and eventually turkey will turn against him.

talk to austria. I am sure he would be willing to help you against turkey. and retreat your fleet back to st.petersburg. we can still maintain peaceful borders. I won#t bother you, you won't bother me.

it's not too late.

keep in mind, the one who asked you to help him was england - he was the one who wanted you to help him, for reasons that help england. he has no interest in your actual position, all he cares for is doing as much damage to me as he can, because he is angry

is that good for you ?

it wasn#t you who approached england "hey, lets go against germany"

it was not your idea, you merely followed englands desperate pleads and promises
you know why he promises so much ? so many "you can keep everything we take of germany, I don't want it anyway" ?

because he wants you to get tempted, and follow the idea without much second thought

think about the future more closely - the moment turkey gets a unit into galicia, you are dead, nothing that can ever be done about that - you don#t want to risk a war on two fronts, now do you ?


so retreat that fleet, and I will forget about that matter. keep it there, and I am sure the results will be different from what england was promising you. you have your hands full already.

and with france on my side, england will not be able to keep his promises.

so concentrate on breaking the austrian - turkisch alliance instead. it will be very troublesome to deal with it, even with a german center or two (and an angry germany wanting it back)
1 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: misorder on my part,
actually next year I may need you to help destroy it for me.
and I have been trying to break them but they haven't replied.
2 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: and where was the fleet originaly headed ?
3 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: ST. P

I'm in another game as Russia which is similarly going bad, the two games mixed in my mind, My apologies.

0 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, has that stiff drink kicked in yet?! I think I can talk Italy down from this, it makes FAR too much sense for him and me to secure our southeast stalemate position and for him to shift at France to help you out while I finish Russia off and then I can help you with Scandinavia eventually... Are you still with us?!
1 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Yes, I'm still with you. I'm going to do my best to hold strong against France and England, but it's anybody's game right now. Except Turkey's.
2 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I wouldn't give Russia much hope either, personally!

I'd be ecstatic with a three-way draw and a middle power alliance has made all the sense in the world to me since day one, so that is my goal... Hopefully Italy will see the light and realize if he leaves France unchecked that France may very well end up with 14,000 points to his name!
3 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, can you imagine Ska attacking Norway? What if Mos supported Norway to Stp while Norwegian slid into Norway? Baltic could cover Swe while Kiel covers Den, Ruh covers Kiel and Sil covers Mun... This could get you to seven centers and a build! Think about it and let me know since Mos hitting Sev would be useful as well, but the highest priority is keeping you as strong as possible, which will also result in you being able to slow down the E/F as much as possible...
4 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: I am 100% aligned with a central powers alliance; France and England are, quite obviously, my biggest threats right now, and I must handle them. I'd love to take St. Pete; I can see that it would help both of us immensely, and if there's something I've learned this game, it's that you put a dying dog out of its misery. If Moscow will support Norway to St. Pete, I will move Norway to St. Pete and NWG to Norway per your suggestion. Similarly, Silesia will move to Munich to help cover my home centers. I've thought long and hard about this, and it is a great plan. I will gladly take your support into St. Pete.

France will get, at most, one build this turn, and after Italy's moves I can see that we are in a delicate situation. In the interest of equal growth, would you consider letting Italy hold onto Trieste, Smyrna and Ankara so that he can equip his western front with enough firepower to push back France? I would consider it a long-term investment in our continued viability, and a strong strategy to contain E/F. I eagerly await your response.
5 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Great, glad you are onboard! Moscow will support you into Stp, that works for both of us as you suggest. France is a HUGE concern and I am in agreement on Italy keeping Trieste, Smy and Ank. Glad the three of us finally appear to be on the same page, I've been pushing this Central Powers alliance since day one, here's to our success!! :-)

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Not stabbing you wouldve worked out even worse, I think. I needed to make sure I at least got one centre from the inevitable divvying up of your empire. Admittedly, I am not in great shape now...I had expected Russia to help me.
No hard feelings?
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Well, you're wrong about how it would have worked out better. First off, you're not going to get that SC because I'm going to be supporting Russia into Trieste (as I warned you).

Propping me up longer would have given France and Germany a chance to come in and relieve pressure. The Russia-turkey juggernaut is on the roll, and you're next. What's worse, you've shown yourself to be totally untrustworthy. I've been communicating with France and Germany and telling them how closely we're working together, so they know that you'll sell out a close ally for just 1 SC.
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I saw no signs of France or germany coming in to relieve pressure. Germany in fact told me he wasn't planning on moving east. His moves in the spring show that. it was clear to me that regardless of whether or not i retreated from Trieste, you couldn't hold off Russia and Turkey and I couldn't help you since my fleets couldnt support your primarily inland holdings. Thus, i needed to get an extra SC so that I could build a third army and stand a better chance against the juggernaut.

Its fair enough that you are helping Russia to take Trieste-- i believed your warning and i guess i expected such action. Obviously, I would rather you spend your resources slowing down the russians or the turks and I would help you in any way I could if you were doing that.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: France has a big northern fleet, and that makes Scandinavia his next likely target. Meanwhile, Russia has troops on 3 sides of Germany, so he better figure it out. Notice that Germany and France both moved fleets out of England--i'm pretty sure they're on the same page.

But about us: I want to stay in the game more than I want to punish you. So if you can explain to me how that is going to happen, I'm listening. But you'll also have to tell me why I shouldn't assume you'll stab me.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I will support your serbian army into greece with F Ion and F Alb.
i will also support your [968909] army into vienna if you want, though i cant imagine that will succeed.

i won't stab you because i cant stab you...you only have centre right now, and i cant get to it. i also wont stab you because i now fully realize the strength of turkey/russia working together. before i thought i could turn russia against turkey, but ive lost faith in that.
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: I appreciate your offer, but it won't work...Turkey can cut your support in Ion and provide a support from either Bul or Aeg.

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> ITALY: Keeping Tyrr Sea intact leads me to believe you're still with me against France, but I'd like to hear from you before moving forward. The positions of your forces look suited to be more pro-tURKISH and anti-FRENCH than otherwise to me, but unless I hear from you I have to operate under the assumption that you're pissed off at me for stealing Naples.

Please contact me and let me know your wants/thoughts/concerns, etc. You probably don't much trust me or France right now, but you do still have options, and I'd hate to see you just give up like Austria did.
1 ITALY -> TURKEY: The only options I have are who do I help or screw more. I'm tired of this.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: The only options I have are who do I help or screw more. I'm tired of this.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: Well, that's what I'm asking - who DO you want to side with? I'm in better position to keep you alive against France than he is positioned to keep you alive against me, if you're interested in surviving. Unfortunately, it sounds like you just want out - in which case I can euthanize you quicker than France can, with two units bordering Venice to his one, and one unit bordering Rome to his none. Whichever way you're leaning, it looks to me like I'm your better bet.

I will attack Venice with my two armies - if you want to die, don't support Piedmont in or move in from Tuscany with Piedmont's support. If you want to live, swing a deal with France and bounce me out.
4 TURKEY -> ITALY: I would also like to submit for your consideration, if I may, that France has done nothing but advance upon you, whereas I did what I could to help you for many years. Which I am still willing to do, if you let me - continued survival or a quick merciful death, whichever you want. But I hope you decide to hang in there and work with me.
5 TURKEY -> ITALY: Ionian and Naples are support-holding Tyrrhenian.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> ITALY: Yes indeed! Can we keep Gas dmz? In return i will supp you to brest if you get into mao
1 ITALY -> GERMANY: I assume you meant Burgundy? I mean, it seems that our strongest moveset is precisely Spain moving to Gascony, so that we can ensure we triumph against Brest in the Autumn.

More specifically, if we order Por-mao, Spa-gas and Par S Spa-gas, England can bounce Por-mao, but can't stop Spa-gas. In the Autumn, England will be forced to choose between support holding Brest or bouncing Por-mao. Even if England decides to defend Brest, this means Por-mao succeeds and we're absolutely certain to get Brest next Spring.

What do you say? Burgundy, as far as I'm concerned, is definitely to be a DMZ!
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: Meanwhile, I'll see if I can get the new fleet to move West, so that England can't hope to retaliate against you.

The issue regarding the East is a bit more complicated, though. I can stall Turkey in the Sea, but how can we best support Austria? Even if Austria can't be propped up indefinitely, we should delay its collapse as much as possible. Do you think we risk Trieste falling and order Ven-tyr? If Trieste makes it, our position is surely stronger to push Russia back.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: Ok spain to gas. I guess you need me to hold back the russians & turks, so i am a better ally for you than the brits.
4 ITALY -> GERMANY: To be perfectly honest, I think you're an ally without which I can't hope to stay in one piece. I've being doing my best to prop Austria, as I can't hope to withstand them without Austria. If, or rather, when, Austria is further weakened, I can't possibly hope to hold my own against Russia and Turkey by my own (nor, as a matter of fact, can you). To make things worse, Russia does not answer me at all, meaning I can't possibly drive a wedge between them. If one of us goes under the bus, so does the other.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: FYI - I think Germany is going to try to solo, beware! I got a message from England, asking if I'd support him into MAO, and he'd support me to Por because England wants to survive. Fair enough, but then Germany sends me a message saying I should consider having England go to MAO, it could help, and even though last time we talked he said he would be okay with me going to Tyrolia, he now asks if it can wait a season or two &and& wants to make sure it's okay if he can go to Gascony, etc., etc. The Germany has the Englishman in his hip pocket, England asked me to help him because England wants to survive this game, but it's not because he's offering to help me solo (which he clearly cannot offer), it's because he has already cut a deal with Germany to help the German solo. Russia may have even cut the same deal, so beware!

PS - Germany once said something to me about being afraid of you moving into Finland, that may actually be a good options at some point, the less comfortable Germany is right now, the less likely he goes for a solo and the more likely we three-way draw.

Thoughts?
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Those are some interesting developments. Let me mull it over. Also, I can't chat much since I'm at work now, but I'll be on later tonight.
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Sounds good. Germany is saying he will draw for sure, but what else is he supposed to say? I'm watching him closely, hopefully I'm just over-reacting.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Overall, I still think we're in pretty good shape. We don't need to push Germany back to be on par with us, we only just need to ensure that he stays under 18 Scs.

Of course, to just hold your end of the line keeping what you currently have, you would need to get fleets into Gol, WMS, and Naf.

Worst-case would be if England and France did everything they could to help Germany solo, which in the near-term would be to help him put a power-3 attack on Spa for the fall. Hopefully, some diplomatic words can rectify this situation. Perhaps, ask Germany not to enter Gas if his intent is to merely draw. Also, England and France might be jaded enough to refuse to cooperate with Germany. How does that situation look as of now?
4 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: On my end of the line, I certainly hope that Russia hasn't made a deal with Germany to make things difficult, but I think I found a set of moves that'll work relatively safely regardless. Tyrolia is a key territory and I can force you in from Ven this Spring, but Boh and even War aren't critical, as we could also just fall back to the Tyr, Vie, Gal, Ukr, Mos line. 0 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Nice to see Norweigan Sea disbanded, so Norway is no longer n immediate danger. It seems that Russia wants to end hostilities with you, and focus on the big threats of Germany and Austria
1 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: It's a shame you and I couldn't come to some understanding before your disband. Taking Bur out of the equation must have been a tough choice.
Have you spoken with Italy? So long as you can get him to back off a little, Germany will not make much progress. I'm pretty sure he intends Munich to move in Sil.
2 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: My Bur disband wasn't pro-gERMANY, in case you though so. I need the MAO fleet to move to Spain, to prevent Mars from going there. Germany has 4 units next to Burgundy, so my army being there couldn't have prevented him from taking it, , and I may have been forced to disband a unit in Spring, which would guarantee me a SC loss in Autumn. Im still very much interested in working with you, the sooner the better, because Germany is the biggest long term threat, whatever short term deals he may offer to any of us.
3 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Okay. Well I'm not hearing much from Germany. Either he's really busy as he claims, or I was right and he's setting himself up to change the tides again.
I will do my best to secure NTH this year. That is my main objective. It should also tell you that you don't have to fear England's fleets for a while at least. Given the first few years, I think it wise to take it one step at a time.
Let me know if you meet with any success where Italy is concerned. Austria's role in this game could also change if Italy was convinced to play otherwise than with Germany.
4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Yeah, I'll definitely keep you informed, both on Italy and otherwise. As of now, Italy seems to agree that Germany should be stopped, and had agreed to help me if I let him take Mars. I will probably support him into Mars this turn, with Gas, while using MAO to cover Spain (that's why i needed to destroy the Bur army).
Of course, you'd told me that Germany was going to give Mars to Italy anyway, so Italy will actually get to make a neutral move, and potentially side with either of me and Germany in the next move.

2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Do you want Aeg to support Tunis to Smyrna?! I've asked Russia to use Sev to hit Black Sea while I support an attack on Bul, so something will have to give!

I've touched base with the German, thanks for passing on his concern, I think our central powers alliance of A/G/I is going to prevail!! :-)
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Hopefully!
As for the next move... Turkey was really pissed about my moves, and has sworn to oppose me, specifically. You can use this to your advantage, I'm sure. (See what a good wingman I am?)

I was thinking that for my spring move, I would attempt a convoy into SYRIA, instead of Smyrna. Getting an army back there would work wonders for us. Now, if I was Turkey, and focusing on stopping Italy, I might consider bouncing Syria and Con in Smyrna. Unlikely, sure, but a possibility since it would cover three spots at once. If you felt like being creative in spring, I think you should support A SYRIA to Smyrna, so that if he moves there my army would definitely land in Syria!
It might also confuse Turkey (or convince him you're opposing me, too). If that move doesn't work in spring, then I'll definitely take a support into Smyrna for the fall.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: My only other concern is France. He claims to be heading West, but if he moves into Tyr next turn he'll definitely have a shot at one of my centers.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: I see that your position isn't as bad as it could be. Galicia can force its way into Ukraine leaving Ukraine with nowhere to go when Turkey moves to Sevastopol. That means that he has to have more units at home than in the front line where he wants them. I also find it humorous that he has bottled up a fleet in Armenia meaning that his armies have to filter their way out through the Balkans in order to do anything effective.

I'm moving units to the stalemate line already. Please don't move to Silesia since I'm going to lock it down on my side. I am moving Munich to Silesia that can be used to support hold at Warsaw if you need it. Denmark is moving to the Baltic in order to get in at Prussia and the North Sea is heading to Edinburgh in order to get the last build needed to secure the line.

Let me know if there's anything else you need from me.
1 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Sounds good. I can't think of anything really. The gambit now is to just hold off as long as I can.
2 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Actually, I don't suppose you'd be willing to move Swe to Bal instead? You have a lot of fleets on my border. :-P
3 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: The North Sea is moving out to Edi. That way, the only unit along your border is the one in Sweden. That should ease your mind a bit. I will, however, have to move out of Sweden if I am to maintain locations of the stalemate line, especially seeing that a breach is about to occur in the west since France has a lack of fleets to fend off Italy.
4 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Sounds good. Thanks for understanding.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I don't think I can stress how important maintaining parity is for me. It's something that's tremendously worrying. I understand your concerns regarding a balance in the East, but I'd really appreciate an overall balance, since an imbalance in the East can be corrected later on much more easily. Is that all right?

My moves this turn were completely stifled. With F Albania, though, I think we can make our devastating attack this turn. I think an attack involving you supporting me into Vienna from Tyrolia, into Serbia from Bulgaria, and into Trieste from Vienna would work. That's, of course, assuming we're both okay with SC parity. What do you think?
1 RUSSIA -> ITALY: How's this: I support you into Vienna, you take Trieste, and you hit Serbia while I take Budapest, then you take Serbia next year?
2 ITALY -> RUSSIA: That would be superb. You're not covering Warsaw, though?

I'm a bit unclear, though, are you okay with the parity thing? My maximal apologies for bringing it up yet again, but I'm still not clear as to what the resolution of the issue was, and I'd like for us to be in agreement!
3 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I'll be covering Warsaw with Silesia.
4 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I'm fine with trying to keep a relative balance in Scs, but I hope you understand my concern with all of your Scs and units being in the East while a third of my units are out in the Atlantic.
5 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I completely understand. We discussed briefly our plans for withdrawing forces after we take Austria, which is something we can hash out further and implement. After Austria, I'd like to shift my focus to the west and take out France and Germany quickly for our draw with England.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: Those removals were....unexpected. LOL. So Moscow is yours and that frees up War and Gal for me to head directly West. A few stabbing opportunities will present themselves to you down south, but hopefully we're good. I think another season or two should see the West in Chaos while you and pick up our steady gains while solidifying them at the same time. Nothing worse than a quick dot grab followed by a quick dot loss.

How do you want to play the south? We can still support into Ionian, but we also may want to cut Alb and Ion while you get Con-smy. I'm open to suggestions.

Oh, and yes, I'll send something down to Serbia. My hands are a bit more tied now, so you may ultimately be the one breaking through with your fleets while I play a steady hold the line approach with my armies. Because once we do break through, the whole thing will collapse. I'm inclined just to play safe the next season or two to let things shake out. What do you think?
1 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: Well, I don't have a huge preference, but I'm not that worried about east med. He might support Ionian with it, but he can't really do much damage.

I think I'd still suggest at Greece go to Ionian and you support that. I'll bring con down to Smy. Worst case is that he ends up in Greece or Aegean, but we can take it back in the fall. I think it's better if we grab Ionian as soon as possible.
2 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: Ok, sounds good. I'll support you into Ionian then. Leave Con empty after if you can, just for comfort sake on my part? :) Can't see a good reason for you to be there unless you can come up with one.
3 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: Yeah I'm leaving con empty. Smy to arm and con to Smy.

We don't want him to be eliminated by italy allowing him to hold out against us for an extended period of time, however we also don't want him to get too powerful and actually be able to pose any sort of threat to us. I am ambivilent about letting him have stp. What are your thoughts?
